All Classes

Class Description
Background
A background object is a type of tile that appears in the game application window.
Camera
The Camera class is responsible for controlling the viewable area while the Kirby character is moving through the level.
DeeSpriteSheet
An object of DeeSpriteSheet has access to the image files that all correspond to the WaddleDee enemy character (entity).
Entity
This abstract class is the blueprint for all moving character objects in the game.
Game
An object of the Game class will create the game application window combining all the information about characters (entities) and level constructs (tiles).
Handler
Contains all the game entities (player, enemy objects) and all the game tiles (platform) and builds the level with these objects.
Id
Contains the identifiers for all types of entity and tile objects.
KeyInput
Handles the keyboard interactions between the user and the movements/animations of the game character.
Kirby
An object of the Kirby class declares and stores the information needed to program a Kirby playable character into the game.
KirbySpriteSheet
An object of KirbySprite has access to the image files that all correspond to the Kirby character (entity).
Message
An object of this class will hold messages that track user action and can be used for Valves.
moveLeftMessage
This class holds message data tracking Kirby's left movement when the user presses the 'A' key.
moveRightMessage
This class holds message data tracking Kirby's right movement when the user presses the 'D' key.
moveUpMessage
This class holds message data tracking Kirby's jumping movement when the user presses the 'W' key.
Platform
Platform object is a type of Tile class that specifies the data specifically for a platform.
Sprite
An object of the Sprite class will have access to ALL the BuffereedImage files that pertain to the Kirby game.
StartGame
Contains the run commands to start the program.
Tile
This abstract class is the blueprint for all static graphic objects in the game.
WaddleDee
An object of the WaddleDee class declares and stores the information needed to program a WaddleDee character into the game.
